TDD exercise complete. All 8 tests for Conway's Game of Life are implemented and passing:

1. ✅ Empty input → empty output
2. ✅ Single cell dies (underpopulation)
3. ✅ Two cells both die (underpopulation)
4. ✅ Block remains unchanged (still life)
5. ✅ Vertical blinker → horizontal blinker (oscillator)
6. ✅ Live cell with 4 neighbors dies (overpopulation)
7. ✅ Dead cell with 3 neighbors births (reproduction)
8. ✅ Negative coordinates handled correctly

Implementation uses sparse representation (Map keyed by `"x,y"` string) and counts neighbor contributions from live cells.
